  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I call eth_sendRawTransaction to my spaceneth node, it gives me a transaction hash, then I spin while asking for the receipt for that transaction hash every 1 second and I get back null every time.\r\nI do see it sealing a block after my eth_sendRawTransaction, like normal.  I just cannot get a receipt back for the transaction.\r\n\r\nInteresting, if I send the transaction again, I don't get an error (which I would expect since the nonce would be too low).\r\nI get the same transaction hash, but still just spins on the receipt.\r\nAh, the specific problem was that I didn't have enough ETH in the account to cover the gas cost.\r\nSo, bug report: eth_sendRawTransaction doesn't return an error if the account doesn't have enough ETH to cover transaction costs.\r\n\r\nI suppose that may be intentional (I can certainly see situations where I want to get the transaction into the pending pool before I fund the account), but the behavior is different from Geth.",
