    "body": "1) Prepare example developer chains (`spaceneth` in Nethermind and its matching solution in `Geth`)\r\n2) Create a raw, signed transaction to send from an account that does not have enough `Ether`\r\n3) Check the behaviour of `Geth`\r\n4) Reproduce exactly the same behaviour in `Nethermind`\r\n\r\nIt is important to note that the current behaviour is as follows:\r\na) Transaction is sent to `TxPool`.\r\nb) `BlockProducer` rejects the transaction as the account has not enough Eth to cover it\r\nc) Transaction stays in `TxPool` until it will be approved in the future.\r\nd) Any subsequent calls lead to the transaction being ignored as a clone of the one already in `TxPool`.\r\n",
